  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-03-05", 
    "text": "Home Office Deduction Act of 1997 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide that a home office qualifies as the principal place of business if: (1) the office is the location where the taxpayer's essential administrative or management activities are conducted on a regular and systematic (and not incidental) basis by the taxpayer; and (2) the office is necessary because the taxpayer has no other location for the performance of the essential administrative or management activities of the business."
